p.span: Hello from Greenville Consolidated School! This is Friday, April 17, 2020. I wanted to connect with families before we all go on a much welcomed April break.

As many of you have seen on our website and Facebook page, Our superintendent - Mr. Chasse announced that we will continue with remote learning until the end of the school year this is in compliance with the Maine Commissioner of Education’s directive.
The good news is that we do have our regularly schedule April break – from Monday, April 20th through Friday, April 24th!

Please continue to check our golakers.org website for updates regarding our food service – breakfast/lunch program. There will be no deliveries over April break – breakfast and lunch meal delivery will resume on Tuesday, April 28th.
Elementary teachers are sending out Q3 report cards and report cards for students in grades 5 through 12 have been emailed to the students’ school email accounts.

We usually hand out report cards to students to deliver home so we are keeping with this practice of delivery - just via email instead of a paper copy handed to your student from their advisor. Please ask your student to share his or her report with you.
I hope you all have a safe and restful break ahead of you. We will be ready to resume school via our current model of remote learning on Monday, April 27th.
Thank you for all of you are doing. We understand this is a huge undertaking.
Approximate Delivery Van Schedules:
Honda Delivery Van Schedule - Linda Hamilton
Blair Hill to Pleasant Street - 9:00 to 9:30
Cheiftan Heights - 9:30 to 10:00
130 Pritham Avenue to Jct Wharf - 10:00 to 10:30
Ford Delivery Van Schedule - Stephanie Elsemore
Eleveth Street and points south to Shirley - 10:00 to 11:00
Rockwood - 11:30 to 12:00

We appreciate your continued support and patience as we try to maintain a consistent delivery schedule. As delivery continues to grow we still could be 5 or 10 minutes off. Thank you for keeping watch for us and giving us a wave ! It helps us stay on schedule and it brightens our day to see that you are safe and well !
NEXT WEEK: APRIL 20 to 24, 2020 - NO MEAL DELIVERIES FOR VACATION WEEK.
MEAL DELIVERY WILL RESUME ON APRIL 28, 2020
If you would like to sign up for delivery or make changes to your delivery please contact us at 695-3708 ext 1 or email: foodservice@ghslakers.org. GO LAKERS !
It was a great feat! Over the past several days all personal, technological and educational materials were delivered to doorsteps!
